@startuml flow-unidirectional-dataflow
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because this is a single closed control loop with swimlane ownership (who runs
'' each step) and a re-entrant "fx dispatch a new event" back-edge; PlantUML's activity (swimlane) syntax
'' draws partitions + the loop-closing arrow cleanly, and lets each lane carry its concept colour.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title re-frame's six dominoes — the closed unidirectional loop\n<latex>\mathrm{view} := f(\mathrm{state})</latex>\nstate only changes by dispatching events

|#EEEBE8|World / DOM|
start
:User acts\n(Ctrl+F, click tab, edit+save file);
:Browser event fires\n→ rf/dispatch [:event ...];
note right: ① EVENT — a reified Command (data, not a call)

|#E2EBF3|re-frame loop|
:② Coeffects gathered\n(:db = current app-db snapshot);
:③ Event handler runs (PURE)\n<latex>(db, fx) := \mathrm{handler}(\mathit{coeffects}, \mathit{event})</latex>;
note right
  Handlers return *data*: a new :db and/or
  a vector of effects. No IO happens here —
  that is what makes replay/time-travel possible.
end note

|#E3E7F2|app-db (ephemeral UI)|
:④a New app-db committed\n(:ui/find, :ui/history, :ui/theme, :ds/rev);

|#E2EBF3|re-frame loop|
:④b Effects handed to fx handlers;

|#EEE6EF|effect world (edge)|
:⑤ Effects execute (IMPURE)\n:ds/transact, :markdown/render,\n:find/run, :theme/apply, :vv/open;
note right
  Some effects dispatch a NEW event when their
  async work completes (e.g. :markdown/render
  → [:content/rendered …]). That is the
  back-edge that closes the loop.
end note

|#E2EBF3|re-frame loop|
:⑥ Subscriptions recompute (memoised)\nthe Observer signal graph;
note right
  Only subs whose inputs changed re-run.
  Conn-reading subs list :<- [:ds/rev], so a
  DataScript transaction (via :ds/changed)
  invalidates exactly them.
end note

|#E3F2ED|view (reagent)|
:Components re-render from subscriptions\n<latex>\mathrm{view} := f(\mathrm{state})</latex>;
:DOM reflects new state;

|#EEEBE8|World / DOM|
if (effect dispatched a follow-up event?) then (yes — back-edge)
  -[#B1951D]-> closes the loop;
  :next [:event ...];
  detach
else (no)
  stop
endif

legend right
  |= Colour |= Lane / concept |
  |<#9F8766>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| World / DOM / filesystem (user + browser events) |
  |<#4F97D7>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| re-frame machinery (dominoes ①②③④b⑥) |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| app-db — ephemeral UI state (domino ④a) |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| DataScript content-cache effect (:ds/transact) |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| reagent view — the f in the loop equation above |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| async fx → follow-up event (the back-edge) |
  Data flows ONE way: event → handler → effect → state → sub → view → (event).
endlegend
@enduml
